UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS - NIGER (TAHOUA)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 3 Sep 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Agence France Presse 2 Sep 2000
Via: Epoca Online 2 Sep 2000 <http://www.epoca.com.br> [in Portuguese]
through ProMED-PORT [English summary by Mod.JW]

Today [2 Sep 2000] national radio announced that 24 people, mostly women,
have died of a mysterious disease in the city of Nadara in the region of
Tahoua, northern Niger.
Symptoms are intense vomiting shortly followed by coma.
A health surveillance group has officially recorded 47 other cases in the
same region of the country. Medical groups have been sent to their aid; the
patients are being sheltered in a warehouse. Preliminary tests have not
been able to identify the cause of the disease.
--
